commit.message:
Make allocation size test use a bit less memory.

This lets it complete with valgrind on a 8GB RAM machine.
Error out if unsigned long int too small.
Add a convenience static initializer definition.
Fix bitfield size computation when number of elements is large (github #20).
Add some test cases for error parameter validations.
Also check that error is not negative.

!(Error >=) 

Error must be strictly smaller than 1.
Larger than 1 is impossible and equal to 1 will make bpe = 0 since log(1) = 0.
Note addition of save and load functions.

bloom_load: return error codes for various file content errors.
bloom_save: mark lines to ignore for coverage.

Remove BITS from Makefile, build platform default.

Pass in desired CFLAGS if there is a need to override.

Change filter size types from int to unsigned int.

This allows for larger bloom filters to be supported.

This changes the public field types in struct bloom so it introduces
an interface incompatibility.

Resolves github issue #14.
